claim.claim-text:
4. The isolated somatic stem cell of claim 3, wherein the cell is obtained by the following procedure:
obtaining from a human subject a bodily fluid sample containing a plurality of cells;
incubating the sample with EDTA in a container until the sample is separated into an upper layer and a lower layer;
collecting the upper layer; and
isolating the somatic stem cell from the upper layer.

10. The population of isolated somatic stem cells of claim 7, wherein the population is obtained by the following procedure:
obtaining from a human subject a bodily fluid sample containing a plurality of cells;
incubating the sample with EDTA in a container until the sample is separated into an upper layer and a lower layer;
collecting the upper layer; and
isolating the population of somatic stem cells from the upper layer.

13. The cell bank of claim 12, wherein each of the plurality of populations of somatic stem cells is obtained by the following procedure:
obtaining from each of different human subjects a blood or bone marrow sample containing a plurality of cells;
incubating the sample with EDTA in a container until the sample is separated into an upper layer and a lower layer;
collecting the upper layer; and
isolating the somatic stem cells from the upper layer.
